There’s something special about wearing an heirloom, especially when it holds memory, meaning, and craftsmanship all at once 🫶

For @vogueindia’s Wedding Atelier pre-event high tea, I wore one of my grandmother’s gara sarees, a piece I’ve always cherished. I styled it with a pearl-embellished choli, her watch, and timeless jewellery  from @thehouseofrose 💎

The evening announced the Vogue Wedding Atelier, coming to New Delhi this August, and this felt like the perfect way to honour the afternoon’s theme Family Heirlooms: Past & Future ✨

Grateful I got to wear something that means so much to me. 🤍 

Thank you for a lovely afternoon @rochelle.pinto @vogueindia 

Glam by @makeoverbykausar

latestPosts.caption:
One year without you, my sweet Bella 🐾🕊️

To my soul dog — it’s been a year since you left, and not a day goes by without aching for your presence. When you passed, my world shattered. You weren’t just a pet — you were my best friend, my partner in crime, my constant, my heart.

You brought joy, mischief, and so much love into our lives. I still feel your cuddles, your playful energy, your quiet understanding. You were right by my side through pregnancy, early motherhood, late-night feeds, and stolen daytime naps — always watching over me and Rehan with that gentle, knowing gaze. You were our protector…. only jumping into Aditya’s lap for reasurance when you were unsure and scared.

Lonavala adventures, chasing squirrels, your happy snores… they live on in my heart. I hope you’re running wild and free in heaven now — tail wagging, ears flopping, chasing birds under endless skies.

I miss you more than words can say. Love you forever, my sweet angel girl 🤍🐶

#BellaForever #SoulDog #OneYearWithoutYou #DogMom #InLovingMemory
